    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2579" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δῶμα</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ατος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δέμω</span>, ‘building’):
          (1) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">house, palace, mansion</span>, often pl., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δώματα</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">house</span> as consisting of
          rooms.—(2) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">room</span>, esp. the largest apartment or men's
          dining-hall (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μέγαρον</span>), <i><span class="en">Od. 22.494</span></i>; so perhaps in pl., <i><span class="en">Il. 1.600</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
